{2: 'Lee', 3: 'This kind of Corrupted were bionic mechanoids called royal guards. They were created to work in the Cultural Restoration Exhibition Hall, responsible for showing different cultures and operating these projectors.', 4: '3'}
{2: 'Lee', 3: "After the outbreak of the virus, M.I.N.D. technology's research was the priority.", 4: '3'}
{2: 'Lee', 3: 'This facility was converted into a M.I.N.D. laboratory, responsible for part of the research process.', 4: '3'}

{2: 'Lee', 3: 'These royal guards may not have their own M.I.N.D. systems installed, but they can still extract Construct consciousness from their M.I.N.D.s and upload it to some central consciousness container.', 4: '3'}
{2: 'Lee', 3: 'Just the one we encountered has already uploaded more than ten consciousness.', 4: '3'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lucia', 3: "If we look at the pattern of the Corrupted so far, they should've destroyed the consciousness directly.", 4: '2'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Lee', 3: 'Hm... So we can only assume this is the work of external interference.', 4: '3'}
